  "id": "22022421536",
  "title": "[ITD] Verify UCIe (VCCC2IA) ITD",
  "description": "<em>(Sections with * are mandatory.  You must fill them in, or say &quot;Not Applicable&quot; or &quot;N/A&quot; if you have seriously considered it and determined there's nothing to say.  Remove these instructions and the explanatory text in each section as you fill things in.)</em><br />\n<br />\n<h4>Flow *</h4>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.8em 0px 0.4em; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Roboto, Calibri, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\" id=\"isPasted\">UCIe D2D Phy requires a fixed voltage targeted to 0.7V.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.8em 0px 0.4em; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Roboto, Calibri, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">The AC noise the phy can absorb at DMR configured speed (up to 16Bb/s) is 40mV pk-pk for any frequency above 20Mhz within temperature range.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.8em 0px 0.4em; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Roboto, Calibri, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">To stand in that spec at the transistor level CBB's Pcode control the TD copmensation of it.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.8em 0px 0.4em; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Roboto, Calibri, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Temperature source:</strong>&nbsp;PCU_CR_DTS_TEMP_SOC(1/2)_CR[1:0][<a href=\"https://docs.intel.com/documents/pm_doc/src/DMR_CBB/HAS/Thermal/DMR%20CBB%20Thermal%20Integration%20HAS/DMR%20CBB%20Thermal%20Integration%20HAS.html#topology-table\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(65, 131, 196); text-decoration: none; cursor: pointer;\">see UCIe/VCCC2IA diodes</a>] contains absolute temperature. Pcode should calculate min, max between them.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.8em 0px 0.4em; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Roboto, Calibri, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Fuse set:</strong>&nbsp;D2D_ITD_CUTOFF_V, D2D_ITD_CUTOFF_V2, D2D_ITD_SLOPE, D2D_ITD_SLOPE2, ITD_CUTOFF_TJ</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.8em 0px 0.4em; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Roboto, Calibri, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">1. Run function from itd.py (description of function: function picks one CCB and iterates through its cores, changing their temperature and comparing the expected voltage compensation to actual voltage compensation)</p><p><br /></p>\n<br />\n<h4>Configuration *</h4>\nHow does the platform need to be configured to obtain the desired coverage? For example: fuses, bios knobs, pre-test scripts, kernel/OS config. In the case of BIOS knobs, list all that impact this coverage, including both custom and default.<br />\n<br />\n<h4>Pass/Fail criteria *</h4>\nExamples: register values to look for, what content output to look for on the screen, key words or sections in the log.<br />\n<p><br /></p><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 12.18px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; display: inline !important; float: none;\" id=\"isPasted\">all IP functional tests are same format, expected voltage within 4mv of actual, that being ITDoffset+(uncompensated voltage, vf curve) == actual(WP or fivr)</span><br />\n<h4>Intent Verification Strategy *</h4>\nHow will TC logic be checked out prior to testing on silicon (e.g. on N-1 hardware, in Simics, etc.)?  If not possible, explain why (e.g. new feature not present in N-1 and not modelled in pre-si environment).<br />\n<p><br /></p><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 12.18px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; display: inline !important; float: none;\" id=\"isPasted\">Simics, expected == actual voltage</span><br />\n<h4>HW Requirements</h4>\nWhat besides silicon is required for execution of this test?  For example: logic analyzer, a thermal head, an Intel test card or IHV device, etc.<br />\nN/A<br />\n<h4>SW Requirements</h4>\nWhat software besides actual test content is needed for execution of this test?  For example: special version of operating system, drivers, firmware, or harassers (to run with the main test content), software tool(s).<br />\nN/A<br />\n<h4>Coverage</h4>\nSpecify any expected coverage that is dependent on environment or configuration (not covered in the TCD's description).  Also specify any coverage assessment/measurement technique that might be used, if applicable and if not stated in the TCD.<br />\n<p><br /></p>nothing new fromGNR-DMR<br />\n<h4>Component Interactions</h4>\nDescribe or illustrate the components that are involved and how they interact. This section is only needed if it provides more information than the TCD article, perhaps specific to the validation environment and framework used for this test_case.<p><br /></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 12.18px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; display: inline !important; float: none;\" id=\"isPasted\">simplified algo: ring.fivr.voltage == ( delta_v * delta_t * </span>ucie.itd.slope.val<span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 12.18px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; display: inline !important; float: none;\" id=\"isPasted\">)+</span>ucie.d2d_fused_voltage.val&nbsp;<span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 12.18px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; display: inline !important; float: none;\" id=\"isPasted\">== </span>ucie.fivr._voltage.val</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px;\" id=\"isPasted\">delta_t= itd_config.cutoff_tj.val - thermals.ucie_minmax_temp._mint.val</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px;\">delta_v=ring.vf_curve.at0.itd.cutoff_v.val - ucie.d2d_fused_voltage.val</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px;\"><br /></p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px;\">dependent variables:</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px;\">itd values:&nbsp;</p><p style=\"margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt\">ucie.itd.cutoff_v.val\n= 1066008576</p><p style=\"margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt\">ucie.itd.cutoff_v2.val\n= 1066008576</p><p style=\"margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt\">ucie.itd.floor_v.val\n= 0</p><p style=\"margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt\">ucie.itd.slope.val =\n991952896</p><p style=\"margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt\">ucie.itd.slope2.val\n= 991952896</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;\">itd_config.cutoff_tj.val\n= 1120534528</p><p style=\"margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt\">ucie.itd.vx.val =\n1120403456</p><p style=\"margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt\"><br /></p><p style=\"margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt\">min temp:</p><p style=\"margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt\">thermals.ucie_minmax_temp._mint.val\n= 1109393408</p><p style=\"margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt\"><br /></p><p style=\"margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt\">actual voltage:</p><p style=\"margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt\">ucie.fivr._voltage.val\n= 1061309440</p><p style=\"margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt\"><br /></p><p style=\"margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt\">expected uncomp voltage:</p><p style=\"margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt\">ucie.d2d_fused_voltage.val\n= 1060372480</p><p style=\"margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt\"><br /></p>